<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="101" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="101">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="101">Blooming in January and February.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" type="observations">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="101">Observations.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="101">
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Tillandsia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tillandsia mauryana" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="mauryana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">Tillandsia mauryana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Lyman B. 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, LB" journalOrPublisher="Journal of The Bromeliad Society" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" refId="B17" refString="Smith, LB, 1937. Studies in the Bromeliaceae VIII. Contributions From the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 117: 31." title="Studies in the Bromeliaceae VIII. Contributions From the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 117: 31." year="1937">Smith (1937)</bibRefCitation>
, based on specimens from the canyon of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Metztitlán">Metztitlan</normalizedToken>
, in the state of Hidalgo, Mexico. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.21829/abm60.2002.901" author="Espejo-Serna, A" journalOrPublisher="Acta Botanica Mexicana" pageId="9" pageNumber="108" pagination="25 - 35" refId="B8" refString="Espejo-Serna, A, 2002. Viridantha un genero nuevo de Bromeliaceae (Tillandsioideae) endemico de Mexico. Acta Botanica Mexicana 60 (60): 25 - 35, DOI: https://doi.org/10.21829/abm60.2002.901" title="Viridantha un genero nuevo de Bromeliaceae (Tillandsioideae) endemico de Mexico." url="https://doi.org/10.21829/abm60.2002.901" volume="60" year="2002">Espejo-Serna (2002)</bibRefCitation>
transferred the species to 
<taxonomicName authority="A.Espejo-Serna, 2002" authorityName="A.Espejo-Serna" authorityYear="2002" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Viridantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Viridantha" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">Viridantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ehlers, R" journalOrPublisher="Sonderheft" pageId="9" pageNumber="108" pagination="1 - 144" refId="B7" refString="Ehlers, R, 2009. Die gruenbluehenden, kleinen, grauen Tillandsien Mexickos. Die Bromelie. Sonderheft 6: 1 - 144" title="Die gruenbluehenden, kleinen, grauen Tillandsien Mexickos. Die Bromelie." volume="6" year="2009">Ehlers (2009)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authority="L. B. Sm." form="secundifolia" genus="T." infraspecific-rank="forma" lsidName="T. mauryana" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" rank="form" species="mauryana">T. mauryana L. B. Sm. forma secundifolia</taxonomicName>
, differentiating it from the typical form only by the secund disposition of its leaves. Besides, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ehlers, R" journalOrPublisher="Sonderheft" pageId="9" pageNumber="108" pagination="1 - 144" refId="B7" refString="Ehlers, R, 2009. Die gruenbluehenden, kleinen, grauen Tillandsien Mexickos. Die Bromelie. Sonderheft 6: 1 - 144" title="Die gruenbluehenden, kleinen, grauen Tillandsien Mexickos. Die Bromelie." volume="6" year="2009">Ehlers (2009)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that its populations grow separated from those of 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. mauryana" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" rank="species" species="mauryana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">T. mauryana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The detailed analysis of the morphological characteristics of living and dried specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="forma mauryana" form="mauryana" genus="T." infraspecific-rank="forma" lsidName="T. mauryana" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" rank="form" species="mauryana">T. mauryana forma mauryana</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName form="secundifolia" genus="T." infraspecific-rank="forma" lsidName="T. mauryana" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" rank="form" species="mauryana">T. mauryana forma secundifolia</taxonomicName>
allowed us to detect that, in addition to the characteristic mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ehlers, R" journalOrPublisher="Sonderheft" pageId="9" pageNumber="108" pagination="1 - 144" refId="B7" refString="Ehlers, R, 2009. Die gruenbluehenden, kleinen, grauen Tillandsien Mexickos. Die Bromelie. Sonderheft 6: 1 - 144" title="Die gruenbluehenden, kleinen, grauen Tillandsien Mexickos. Die Bromelie." volume="6" year="2009">Ehlers (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, there are other differences in the plants of both populations such as: the shape of the rosettes (falcate vs. spherical); the length (1-1.2 cm vs. 1.5-2.5 cm) and the shape (broadly oblong to square vs. broadly elliptic) of the leaf sheaths; the length of the floral bracts (1.8-2 cm vs. 1-1.5 cm), the presence or not of a keel on the floral bracts (absent or visible only in the apex vs. present along the bract); and the colour of the anthers (pale to dark green vs. black).
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">
<taxonomicName authority="A.Espejo-Serna, 2002" authorityName="A.Espejo-Serna" authorityYear="2002" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Viridantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Viridantha grandispica" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandispica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">Viridantha grandispica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ehlers) Hern.-
<normalizedToken originalValue="Cárdenas">Cardenas</normalizedToken>
, Espejo &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="López-Ferr">Lopez-Ferr</normalizedToken>
., 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. rzedowskiana" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" rank="species" species="rzedowskiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">V. rzedowskiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hern.-
<normalizedToken originalValue="Cárdenas">Cardenas</normalizedToken>
, Espejo &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="López-Ferr">Lopez-Ferr</normalizedToken>
. and 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. teloloapanensis" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" rank="species" species="teloloapanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">V. teloloapanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ehlers &amp; Lautner) Hern.-
<normalizedToken originalValue="Cárdenas">Cardenas</normalizedToken>
, Espejo &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="López-Ferr">Lopez-Ferr</normalizedToken>
., are other species morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. secundifolia" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" rank="species" species="secundifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">V. secundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphological differences amongst Viridantha grandispica, V. mauryana, V. rzedowskiana, V. secundifolia and V. teloloapanensis." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/3903133EE608DDEC6D5A005FF20C42DD" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" tableUuid="3903133EE608DDEC6D5A005FF20C42DD">1</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="A.Espejo-Serna, 2002" authorityName="Hern. - Cardenas, Espejo &amp; Lopez-Ferr., comb. et" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Ehlers" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Viridantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Viridantha secundifolia" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="secundifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">Viridantha secundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. grandispica" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" rank="species" species="grandispica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">V. grandispica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of the rosettes (falcate vs. spherical); in the shape of the leaf sheaths (broadly oblong to square vs. narrowly oblong); in the presence or not of a keel on the floral bract (absent or visible only in the apex vs. present along the bract); and in the shape of the sepals (lanceolate vs. ovate). 
<taxonomicName authority="A.Espejo-Serna, 2002" authorityName="Hern. - Cardenas, Espejo &amp; Lopez-Ferr., comb. et" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Ehlers" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Viridantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Viridantha secundifolia" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="secundifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">Viridantha secundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. rzedowskiana" pageId="2" pageNumber="101" rank="species" species="rzedowskiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">V. rzedowskiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of the rosettes (falcate vs. spherical); in the size of the leaf sheaths (1-1.2 cm 
<pageBreakToken pageId="3" pageNumber="102" start="start">
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
</pageBreakToken>
0.8-1.1 cm vs. 1.8-2 cm 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-1.7 cm); in the keel of the floral bract (absent or visible only in the apex vs. present along the bract); and in the shape of the sepals (lanceolate vs. ovate). 
<taxonomicName authority="A.Espejo-Serna, 2002" authorityName="Hern. - Cardenas, Espejo &amp; Lopez-Ferr., comb. et" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Ehlers" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Viridantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Viridantha secundifolia" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="secundifolia">
